<title type="html"><![CDATA[eprom eraser]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=333&amp;p=2849#p2849"><![CDATA[
I put together the simplest eprom eraser I could think of. I ordered a UVC fluorescent tube from the aquarium store I go to and bought a cheap little fixture from the local hardware place. I think the bulb was $20 and the fixture was $10 (Canadian $). I just lean the EPROM's next to the bulb, wait 20 minutes and it works every time. On my bulb I can fit 10 EPROM's at a time (32 pin ones). I could put more in if I modified the fixture.<p>Statistics: Posted by Guest — Sun Jul 17, 2005 9:56 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
