<title type="html"><![CDATA[I finally hacked together an NROM EPROM cart (yay!)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=333&amp;p=2239#p2239"><![CDATA[
If you plan on doing a lot of chip erasing, I'd go with a Flashrom instead, like the 29F040.  Any 32-pin ROMs will need to be rewired anyways AFAIK, might as well rewire the socket a bit more to get the easier erases with flash (also tie /WR to VCC).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10">Memblers</a> — Fri Jun 03, 2005 6:42 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
